The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing was done, just a bit of decoration.
Remove the terrible electric fireplace and the mantle. Stud the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Build a custom closet.
We always start with a quick sketch...
The dirty step is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the flue; all dried out :(
Ready for the plasterer next week
Excited about the little nook on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a lovely little ventilation grille to prevent the chimney from taking in moisture
The flue installer took care of the cap and hood. It should be a bit safer for the crows who nest up there 🪦
The plasterer is done. We're installing the floor tomorrow!
The cork underlayer is laid. I improvised a wood chip vacuum with a roll of toilet paper as an accessory 🤭
A portion of the boards has been sorted and is ready to be laid. Just taking a tea break
Well, progress was slow today due to super delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being laid). @user45@twitter.com had some choice words for me
Done, but on the verge of collapse! Cherry on top: the absurd instructions for mounting the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Left to do the hallway floor, all the baseboards. The decorator is coming in a month, so for now, at home, it's the chic of bare plaster
Slightly longer evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw/miter saw where we want the floor to be perfectly flush.
The cork underlayment for the hallway is also laid
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then departure at 5 AM this morning to pick up Thing 1 at Heathrow, then nap and finishing touches for the hallway; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing when the glue sets.
